Isabel sold a total of 3 bead necklaces and 3 gemstone necklaces. Since each necklace was priced at $6, the first step is to calculate the total number of necklaces sold:

$$
3 \text{ (bead necklaces)} + 3 \text{ (gemstone necklaces)} = 6 \text{ necklaces}
$$

Next, multiply the total number of necklaces by the price per necklace:

$$
6 \text{ necklaces} \times 6 \text{ dollars per necklace} = 36 \text{ dollars}
$$

Thus, Isabel earned $36 by selling the necklaces.

Answer: \boxed{36}
